subSubSection.paragraph:
Variation.There is some variation in the amount of dark brown scales on the forewings. In some specimens they form a dark apical streak. Freshly emerged specimens are more greyish compared with specimens in collections. Specimens from Greece (Olympos) are slightly larger (wingspan 14-16 mm), slightly more broad-winged and with fewer dark scales on the forewing (thereby resembling 
M. leuca
) but the reduction of dark scales may be due to worn specimens.
